<link href="adcp.css" rel="stylesheet"><entry><xh5> at the cutting edge of something • on the knifeedge of something</xh5><p> <i>at the cutting edge of something</i>—(also: on the cutting edge of something) involved in the most advanced developments in a particular field: It is unrealistic to expect to be <u>at the cutting edge of</u> the fashion industry for anything longer than fifteen years.</p><p> <i>on the knife-edge of something</i>—(also: on the razor’s edge of something) on the brink of smth. bad or dangerous: The expansion of trade hasn’t closed the gap between those who live on the cutting edge of the global economy and the billions who live <u>on the knife-edge of</u> survival.</p> </entry>
